narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Assessing the history of concepts in the rationalist canon. Distinguishing between historically distinct "takes" on similar or identical concepts. Ultimately, grasping the contribution of rationalist thought to modern philosophy.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: strengths: careful reconsideration of interpretative norms. weaknesses: class was too large; and despite aspirations to critique of the rationalist canon, the class was fairly conservative in its assessment of canonical texts; no new interpretative frameworks were appealed to or conceived.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! Prof. Della Rocca is a fabulous teacher and will open your mind to ideas that you thought were ridiculous but aren't.
